      Current Contractor, more than 1 year

      Please reconsider

      8 Mar 2023 - Postmarket Surveillance Analyst in Plano, TX
      Recommend
      CEO Approval
      Business Outlook

      Pros

      - good pay but that depends on your contracting agency - coworkers are wonderful people - frequent company events

      Cons

      - 17 people quit within the span of a few months. this was not relayed to ANY of us until AFTER a month of working here. during interview i asked if a position opened because someone left or because the company was expanding and i was lied to and told it was because of expansion. - training is awful. they will give you little to no guidance on how to do your job and then act shocked when you make a mistake. - a few of the more seasoned employees are bullies to the new folks. - management doesnt care to hear any other perspective besides their own. - they knowingly give you too much work and expect you to work overtime to keep up. we had people working 15 hour days 7 days a week just to keep up. they were salary and were not getting paid for overtime. - management changes and bends the rules as they see fit, and you are expected to keep us with this and not ask questions because they never budge. - contract employers had a piece of cake dangled in front of them for permanent positions that never came and were treated like second class citizens - management reprimands you if you can't meet their arbitrary metrics but never question their role in it or how they can help - dinosaur technology that is slow and deletes your work, putting you even more behind - unequal work distribution

      Current Employee, more than 3 years

      Good Company - Too Demanding

      30 May 2023 - Controls Engineer in Columbus, OH
      Recommend
      CEO Approval
      Business Outlook

      Pros

      - Flexibility in work schedule. - Plenty of room for advancement. - Never left on your own, plenty of resources available to you. - Fast paced work environment in the plant. - Such a large company that changing careers is very easy if desired.

      Cons

      - Pay grade structure naturally pushes people towards management if looking to move up quickly. - Pay grades are shared company wide and aren’t tied to responsibility. - People change jobs too frequently which leads to a lot of inconsistency. - Pay vs hours worked in some roles is pretty poor. Incentivizes doing less instead of more.
